qas.question: What name for Tibet most clearly includes the entire Tibetan plateau?
What is another pre-modern Chinese name for Tibet?
Who fought to revive the term Xizang?
What word is Xizang the modern version of?
What does Tubote include instead of the entire Tibetan plateau?

context: Other pre-modern Chinese names for Tibet include <a2_0>Wusiguo<a2_0/> (Chinese: 烏斯國; pinyin: Wūsīguó; cf. Tibetan dbus, Ü, [wyʔ˨˧˨]), Wusizang (Chinese: 烏斯藏; pinyin: wūsīzàng, cf. Tibetan dbus-gtsang, Ü-Tsang), Tubote (Chinese: 圖伯特; pinyin: Túbótè), and Tanggute (Chinese: 唐古忒; pinyin: Tánggǔtè, cf. Tangut). <b3_0>American Tibetologist<b3_0/> <a0_0>Elliot Sperling<a0_0/> has argued in favor of a recent tendency by <b4_0>some authors writing in Chinese<b4_0/> to revive the term <b5_0>Tubote<b5_0/> (simplified Chinese: 图伯特; traditional Chinese: 圖伯特; pinyin: Túbótè) for modern use in place of Xizang, on the grounds that <a1_0>Tubote<a1_0/> more clearly includes the entire Tibetan plateau rather than simply the <b6_0>Tibet Autonomous Region.<b6_0/>[citation needed]
